<title>HUNGARY: Scala sets $15 mln capital increase.</title>
<headline>Scala sets $15 mln capital increase.</headline>
<dateline>BUDAPEST 1996-12-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hungary-based software company Scala ECE said its directors approved a $15 million capital increase.</p>
<p>&quot;This increase will make us very strong financially and enable us to make further heavy investments in products and market development,&quot; chief executive Andreas Kemi said a statement.</p>
<p>The company, whose directors approved the issue on Monday, said the issue was oversubscribed on the first day.</p>
<p>Scala shares were trading at 1505.0 schillings on the Vienna bourse.</p>
